# Production runtime data (when the git working tree root on the server is /opt/msm or similar)
# These MUST be protected so that `git clean -fd` (even on prod deploys) does not delete servers, DBs, logs or community blueprints.
# Note: git clean -fd by default respects .gitignore and will NOT remove these.
/servers/
/backups/
/blueprints/
/.setup_completed
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
